commit.message:
Fix quirk with 2-char single line comment

- Was being interpreted as a block comment because a string is actually
  a list of chars in python!

Merge pull request #24 from MilesCranmer/dev

Add comments for more languages and fix single-line comment quirks

- Add comment characters for CUDA, Makefile filetypes
- Add search mapping for Makefile (search query has "make" -> "Makefile")
- Force lower case on all language options (in case someone writes "CPP")
- Fix quirk with single-line comment getting prepended to start of a code block

Fix single-line comment issue

- First line of code was getting a comment char in front of it
Better comments, only load 1 question url
Add mapping and comment for Makefiles
Add cuda comments, remove case sensitivity

Merge pull request #22 from MilesCranmer/dev

Add option for no language
- Call "--language no", "none", or "nothing" for no language to be appended to your search, no comments to wrap answer text
Add optional key mapping to README
Fix single-line comment being on above line
Finished a TODO, added a TODO
